{"id": "EUVD-2025-12932", "enisaUuid": "07bee9ca-1a2b-355d-af61-71834125b106", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncan: dev: fix skb drop check\n\nIn commit a6d190f8c767 (\"can: skb: drop tx skb if in listen only\nmode\") the priv->ctrlmode element is read even on virtual CAN\ninterfaces that do not create the struct can_priv at startup. This\nout-of-bounds read may lead to CAN frame drops for virtual CAN\ninterfaces like vcan and vxcan.\n\nThis patch mainly reverts the original commit and adds a new helper\nfor CAN interface drivers that provide the required information in\nstruct can_priv.\n\n[mkl: patch pch_can, too]", "datePublished": "2025-05-01T14:09:58", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T17:00:34", "baseScore": 7.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49844", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/386c49fe31ee748e053860b3bac7794a933ac9ac", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ae64438be1923e3c1102d90fd41db7afcfaf54cc"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49844", "GHSA-jjg4-p57c-87j3"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.0, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2924dae9-e616-35db-bfbf-1b04dd6086c9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1"}, {"id": "335ce08c-d1be-31fd-a4b6-63c41d124081", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a6d190f8c7670068d8c154ef8477eca07b5e3574 <386c49fe31ee748e053860b3bac7794a933ac9ac"}, {"id": "71269eed-578e-328c-a186-7a80b9240d92", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.0"}, {"id": "801b677c-90f7-3ae7-8869-a301484dc004", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "e9a7af96-c076-3712-a652-fb6cbb3c9367", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a6d190f8c7670068d8c154ef8477eca07b5e3574 <ae64438be1923e3c1102d90fd41db7afcfaf54cc"}, {"id": "fdcb4d82-80ae-31eb-a2eb-45671abac1b2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.9"}],